@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Carrelage" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Carrelage runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a part of the bar, this will make the bar
rotate by 90 degrees in a clockwise manner around the tile you
clicked on... of course, there must be a tile located at the next
position the bar will go to, otherwise, the bar will not move...

  To complicate or simplify matters, which one you prefer; some
tiles may have arrows on them (represented by triangular shapes).
When the bar touches such a tile, the bar will move in the
direction the arrow is pointing. Also, there may be some 'cracked'
tiles; as long as part of the bar remains on such a tile, it acts
like a normal tile, but when the bar leaves the tile, that tile
will disappear...

  Another tile is a 'switch' tile, it is hidden somewhere on a
normal tile. When the bar gets on that tile, some other tiles,
which are also hidden, will appear. This can make the game easier
to complete. Though, on some other game boards, that tile have to
be found so the bar can access to the otherwise inaccessible exit
tile...

  The goal is to move the bar so part of it is placed on the exit
tile, which is indicated by a 'pressed down' rectangle, in the
least of moves...

  Have fun!

OPTIONS
-------

  Replay: To restart the current game board, but beware: the amount
          of moves you made up to now on that particular game board
          will be accumulated...

  Colour: To change the colour of the bar.  

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

